        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 24 at 6:21PM CDT until August 24 at 7:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Wheeler County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Hemphill County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 715 PM CDT.

* At 621 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 5 miles northwest
of Reydon, or 20 miles west of Cheyenne, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Allison.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
